        <div class="bento-cta">neilpatel.com/ubersuggest <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card">
        <div class="bento-num">✗</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Skip Ubersuggest if</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">You need <span class="accent">accurate traffic data, serious backlinks, or content publishing.</span></h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Agencies managing 50+ sites, competitive link-building campaigns, enterprise teams, and anyone who needs content written and published automatically.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See why theStacc fits better <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS UBERSUGGEST -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">What is Ubersuggest</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">An <span class="accent">all-in-one SEO platform</span> built for the budget-conscious beginner.</h2>
      <p>Ubersuggest was originally created in 2010 by Alessandro Martin as a keyword suggestion tool and acquired by Neil Patel in 2017. It has since expanded into a full SEO suite covering keyword research, site audits, backlink analysis, rank tracking, and content ideas. Owned by NP Digital and headquartered in Los Angeles, the platform pulls from a database of 100 million+ keywords across 140+ countries. Its core value proposition: professional-grade SEO data without the Ahrefs or Semrush price tag.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">The keyword research engine is the strongest part of the product — generating an average of 5,325 related keywords per seed term with 83% volume accuracy in independent testing. That's good enough for most small businesses to build a solid content plan.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">The weaknesses are clear and worth knowing upfront: traffic estimates are only 50.1% accurate (directional at best), the backlink database is 60–70% smaller than Ahrefs, and there's no API, no Zapier, and no content publishing. If those constraints don't eliminate your use case, Ubersuggest is genuinely solid value.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROS / CONS -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The honest pros & cons</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">What Ubersuggest gets right — <span class="accent">and where it lets you down.</span></h2>
      <p>We tested keyword research depth, audit quality, rank tracking, and the lifetime deal math. Here's what we found.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Pros</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Where Ubersuggest shines</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Five genuine strengths worth knowing about.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Cheapest entry into professional SEO tools</h4>
              <p>At $29/month, Ubersuggest is the most affordable full-featured SEO platform on the market. For beginners who can't justify $99–$139/month on Moz or Ahrefs, this is meaningful.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Strong keyword research volume with 83% accuracy</h4>
              <p>Generates 5,325+ related keywords per seed term. The 83% search volume accuracy is competitive — better than free tools, good enough for content planning in most niches.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Lifetime deal option eliminates recurring costs</h4>
              <p>A one-time payment of $290–$990 (depending on tier and promotion) eliminates the monthly subscription forever. For long-term users, the payback period is under a year.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Beginner-friendly interface with no overwhelming data tables</h4>
              <p>The UI is clean and approachable. No cascading data tables, no cryptic metrics. New users can get their first keyword list in under 10 minutes — which isn't true of Ahrefs or Semrush.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Daily rank tracking included on all paid plans</h4>
              <p>Most tools at this price point update rankings weekly. Ubersuggest tracks daily across all tiers — a genuine advantage for monitoring new content performance.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Cons</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Where Ubersuggest falls short</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Five honest weaknesses we ran into.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Traffic estimates are only 50.1% accurate</h4>
              <p>Directional at best. If you're making content investment decisions based on Ubersuggest's traffic projections, you're working with a coin flip. Treat them as rough indicators, not numbers.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Keyword difficulty scores skew low</h4>
              <p>Consistently underestimates difficulty compared to Ahrefs and Semrush. New users often target keywords that look achievable in Ubersuggest but are actually highly competitive.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Backlink database is 60–70% smaller than Ahrefs</h4>
              <p>For competitive link analysis and backlink prospecting, the data gaps are significant. Don't use Ubersuggest to evaluate a competitor's full link profile — you'll miss too much.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Doesn't write, edit, or publish content</h4>
              <p>Ubersuggest surfaces content ideas and article outlines. That's where it stops. You write every word, edit every draft, and publish everything yourself. No automation, no output.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>No API, no Zapier, no workflow integrations</h4>
              <p>Can't pipe data anywhere. No custom automations, no agency reporting pipelines, no Slack alerts. For solo operators this doesn't matter — for agencies managing multiple clients, it's a dealbreaker.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
